plugins.title: BigQuery
plugins.description: Interact with your BigQuery data using natural language. This MCP server allows you to securely connect to your datasets to search the datasets, inspect table metadata, execute SQL queries, generate time-series forecasts, and perform contribution analysis directly from your AI tools.

variables.name: <BIGQUERY_PROJECT>
variables.title: BigQuery Project ID
variables.description: The GCP project ID.

variables.name: <BIGQUERY_LOCATION>
variables.title: BigQuery Location
variables.description: (Optional) The location of your BigQuery dataset (e.g. "US", "EU").

plugins.title: AlloyDB for PostgreSQL
plugins.description: Interact with your AloyDB for PostgreSQL data using natural language. This MCP server allows you to securely connect to your database for executing SQL queries, inspecting table schemas, analyzing query plans, and troubleshooting database performance issues directly from your AI tools.

variables.name: <ALLOYDB_POSTGRES_PROJECT>
variables.title: AlloyDB Project ID
variables.description: The GCP project ID.

variables.name: <ALLOYDB_POSTGRES_REGION>
variables.title: AlloyDB Region
variables.description: The region of your AlloyDB instance.

variables.name: <ALLOYDB_POSTGRES_CLUSTER>
variables.title: AlloyDB Cluster ID
variables.description: The ID of your AlloyDB cluster.

variables.name: <ALLOYDB_POSTGRES_INSTANCE>
variables.title: AlloyDB Instance ID
variables.description: The ID of your AlloyDB instance.

variables.name: <ALLOYDB_POSTGRES_DATABASE>
variables.title: AlloyDB Database Name
variables.description: The name of the database.

variables.name: <ALLOYDB_POSTGRES_USER>
variables.title: AlloyDB Database User
variables.description: (Optional) The database username. Defaults to IAM authentication if unspecified.

variables.name: <ALLOYDB_POSTGRES_PASSWORD>
variables.title: AlloyDB Database Password
variables.description: (Optional) The password for the database user. Defaults to IAM authentication if unspecified.

variables.name: <ALLOYDB_POSTGRES_IP_TYPE>
variables.title: AlloyDB IP Type
variables.description: (Optional) The IP type i.e. “Public” or “Private”. Defaults to "Public" if unspecified.
